ts were rewarded with all five judges scoring it in her favour.\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 715, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Dubliner_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9999983408320199, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Dubliner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Dubliner_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Dubliner_(magazine)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her moments\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"Valdes Pana\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 797}, {\"ngram\": \"her first round efforts\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 838}, {\"ngram\": \"all five judges\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"her favour\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The second followed a similar pattern with the experienced Harrington continuing to box clever and remaining considered with the timing of when to come forward.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_F._Harrington\", \"score\": 0.9999969710679977, \"rank\": 1.5895289554232724e-06, \"text\": \"Harrington\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_F._Harrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_F._Harrington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The second\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"a similar pattern\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 938}, {\"ngram\": \"the timing\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This round was deemed closer with the 34-year-old shading it 3-2 on the judges' cards.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This round\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"the 34-year-old shading\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"the judges' cards\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1147}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final round saw Harrington maintain her distance against the Colombian who was desperately seeking a route back into the contest only to encounter counters as the champion from Tokyo laid traps, ultimately winning the final round convincingly on all the judges' cards.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_F._Harrington\", \"score\": 0.9999969710679977, \"rank\": 1.5895289554232724e-06, \"text\": \"Harrington\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_F._Harrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_F._Harrington\"}, {\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.649274574200558e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The final round\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"her distance\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"the Colombian\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1224}, {\"ngram\": \"a route\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"the contest\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1282}, {\"ngram\": \"counters\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"the champion\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"the final round\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1383}, {\"ngram\": \"all the judges' cards\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the afternoon,JudeGallagherexited Paris 2024 at the last-16 stage after suffering a defeat by unanimous decision to Carlo Palaam of the Philippines in the men's 57kg category.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1571, \"end\": 1582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9998592549352271, \"rank\": 0.00013381717147405248, \"text\": \"Philippines\